To verify that the container is running you can type the following command:  docker ps  which output should be similar to the following:  CONTAINER ID        IMAGE                        COMMAND                  CREATED             STATUS                   PORTS                                                                                              NAMES
cfc4a7fb23d0        openbaton/standalone:latest   /usr/bin/supervisord    49 seconds ago      Up 49 seconds            0.0.0.0:5672- 5672/tcp, 0.0.0.0:8080- 8080/tcp, 0.0.0.0:8443- 8443/tcp, 0.0.0.0:15672- 15672/tcp   openbaton  The standalone container uses the standard debian packages for installing the open baton components, thus logs are available under /var/log/openbaton. To connect to the running container containing Open Baton you can type the following command:  docker exec -ti openbaton bash  To stop and delete the running Open Baton container you can type respectively the following commands:  docker stop openbaton
