Once the Network Service Record went to "ACTIVE" your  OpenIMSCore  -  Bind9  -  FHoSS  deployment is finished.   To test your  OpenIMSCore  you may use a Sip client of your choice. Be sure to use the realm defined in your  Bind9 Virtual Network Function Descriptor  while testing registration and call. By default the  FHoSS  conaints 2 users : alice and bob. The user is the same as the password, but you may also alter it to your needs modifying the  FHoSS Virtual Network Function Descriptor  ( You will find the users in "var_user_data.sql" file under the fhoss folder)  For Benchmarking we can use  IMS Bench SIPp  but then you should add more users to the  FHoSS  database since by default it only contains 2 users.    
